# Gunner — Playbook Compliance Rules

## The Four-Layer Architecture

Every label, name, list, color, and configuration value in Gunner must flow through the playbook resolution chain:

```
User Playbook > Tenant Playbook > Industry Playbook > Software Playbook
```

The most specific layer always wins. Pages are DUMB — they display what the playbook says. The system is SMART.

## The Compliance Checklist

Run this mentally before writing ANY string, array, or object in a component or router:

| What you're writing | Where it must come from |
|---|---|
| A label or terminology word | `useTenantConfig().t.*` |
| A role name | `useTenantConfig().roles` |
| A stage name or color | `useTenantConfig().stages` |
| A call type name | `useTenantConfig().callTypes` |
| A KPI metric name or list | `useTenantConfig().kpiMetrics` |
| A roleplay persona | `useTenantConfig().roleplayPersonas` |
| A market or lead source | `useTenantConfig().markets` / `.leadSources` |
| A funnel stage label | `useTenantConfig().kpiFunnelStages` |
| A grading rubric criterion | Loaded in `grading.ts` from industry/tenant playbook |
| An algorithm threshold | `SOFTWARE_PLAYBOOK` constants in `playbooks.ts` |

## Banned Patterns — Never Write These

### Hardcoded stage codes (outside schema.ts and playbooks.ts)
```
"new" "lead" "contacted" "qualified" "offer" "under_contract"
"new_lead" "appointment_set" "offer_made" "dispo" "closing" "closed" "dead"
```

### Hardcoded role names (outside seeds and playbooks)
```
"Acquisition Manager" "Lead Manager" "Generator" "Dispo"
"acquisition_manager" "lead_manager" "generator" "dispo"
```

### Hardcoded call types (outside seeds and playbooks)
```
"cold_call" "warm_call" "inbound" "follow_up" "offer_call" "dispo_call"
"Acquisition Call" "Follow Up" "qualification"
```

### Hardcoded terminology (use t.* from useTenantConfig instead)
```
"property" "properties" "lead" "leads" "deal" "deals" "walkthrough"
```
Use: `t.asset`, `t.assetPlural`, `t.contact`, `t.contactPlural`, `t.deal`, `t.dealPlural`

### Hardcoded tenant IDs (outside seeds)
```
tenantId: 1    tenantId: 450029    tenantId: 540044
```

## How to Add a New Playbook-Driven Field

Follow this exact sequence — skip no steps:

1. **`shared/types.ts`** — Add the field to the relevant interface (`IndustryPlaybook`, `TenantPlaybook`, or `Terminology`)
2. **`server/seeds/reWholesaling.ts`** — Add the value to the RE Wholesaling seed
3. **`server/services/playbooks.ts`** — Add a `resolveX()` function with the 4-layer precedence
4. **`server/routers/playbook.ts`** — Add the resolved field to the `getConfig` response object
5. **`client/src/hooks/useTenantConfig.ts`** — Expose the field with a typed default
6. **Component** — Use the hook value. Never hardcode.

